asn1_strerror(3)                                                        libtasn1                                                        asn1_strerror(3)

NAME
       asn1_strerror - API function

SYNOPSIS
       #include <libtasn1.h>

       const char * asn1_strerror(int error);

ARGUMENTS
       int error   is an error returned by a libtasn1 function.

DESCRIPTION
       Returns a string with a description of an error.  This function is similar to strerror.  The only difference is that it accepts an error (number)
       returned by a libtasn1 function.

RETURNS
       Pointer to static zero-terminated string describing error code.

SINCE
       1.6

